    "comment": "Rationale: An antibody specific for the C-terminal end of mGluR4 was raised and was shown to be specific (see Fig. 2A showing lack of signal in mGluR4 -/- mice and 2B showing signal only in COS cells expressing mGluR4).\n\nImmunogold and immunoperoxidase treatment of various brain sections were then images using electron microscopy indicated that mGluR4 was present in the membrane of the presynapse in cerebellum (Fig. 4), striatum (Fig. 5), ventral palladium (VP) (Fig. 6), SNr(Fig. 7), CA1 (Fig. 8 and 9), and DG (Fig. 10). The authors observed differences in synapse formation with cerebellar cortex forming Type I (asymmetical), striatum and VP forming Type II (symmetric) and hippocampal and SNr forming both.\n\n20/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials & Methods: Several brain areas from rat (two adult Sprague^Dawley) and\nmouse (two adult mGluR4+/+ and two adult mGluR4-/-).",
